#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:9
msgid "Multiple Materials"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:11
msgid ""
"Normally, different colors or patterns on an object are achieved by adding "
"textures to your materials. However, in some applications you can obtain "
"multiple colors on an object by assigning different materials to the "
"individual faces of the object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:19
msgid "Add new material"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:22
msgid ""
"To apply several materials to different faces of the same object, you use "
"the Material Slots options (3) in the Materials header panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:28
msgid "Material menu in edit mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:31
msgid ""
"The workflow for applying a second material to some faces of an object "
"covered by a base material is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:35
msgid ""
"In Object mode, apply the base material to the whole object (as shown in "
":doc:`Assigning a material </materials/assigning_a_material>`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:36
msgid ""
"Create/select the second material (the whole object will change to this new "
"material)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:37
msgid "In the Active Material box (2), re-select the base material."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:38
msgid ""
"Go to Edit Mode - Face Select (a new box appears above the Active Material "
"box with Assign/Select/Deselect)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:39
msgid "Select the face/faces to be colored with the second material."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:40
msgid ""
"In the Object Material Slots box (3), click the :kbd:`+` to create a new "
"slot, and while this is still active, click on the second material in the "
"Available Materials list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:41
msgid ""
"Click the Assign button, and the second material will appear on the selected"
" object faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:44
msgid ""
"You can also make this new material a copy of an existing material by adding"
" the data block:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/materials/multiple_materials.rst:46
msgid ""
"Select object, get the material, (R Click) - Copy data to clipboard. When "
"you have renamed the material, click \"Data - Data\" to link to the existing"
" material. Proceed to assign faces as required. NB: If you change the "
"material on the original object, the new object color changes too."
msgstr ""
